## Phase 2: Create App Icons

Your app needs icons in multiple sizes for different devices. Here's how to generate them all quickly.

**Step 1 — Create one high quality icon**

Design a 512x512 pixel PNG icon for your app. You can do this free at canva.com — make a square design with a dark navy background (`#060d1a`) and a gold/white tax or government symbol in the center.

**Step 2 — Generate all sizes automatically**

Go to pwabuilder.com/imageGenerator or realfavicongenerator.net. Upload your 512x512 image and it will generate all the sizes you need in one download.

**Step 3 — Add icons to your project**

1. Inside your `public/` folder, create a new folder called `icons`
2. Copy all the downloaded icon files into `public/icons/`

Your `public/` folder should now look like:
```
public/
├── icons/
│   ├── icon-72x72.png
│   ├── icon-96x96.png
│   ├── icon-128x128.png
│   ├── icon-192x192.png
│   └── icon-512x512.png
├── index.html
└── manifest.json